The paper deals with the problem of binary similarity, which is a crucial issue in several application scenarios, such as copyright disputes, malware analysis, vulnerability detection, etc. The proposed solution involves creating an embedding model that maps binary functions into vectors in $\mathbb{R}^{n}$, which captures syntactic and semantic similarity between binaries. This approach is related to several subfields of computer science, such as cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
